You are working on a Senior Analytics Engineer technical assessment for Radius.
The deliverable will be reviewed by a Senior Tech Lead and defended in a live session.
The runtime environment was provided by Radius and is OPINIONATED — respect their conventions.

PROJECT IDENTITY:
- dbt project name: "mercado"
- dbt project location: dbt_project/mercado/
- Python package location: src/mercado/
- Variables and column names: SPANISH (matches Radius profiles.yml)
- Documentation: SPANISH (audience is Mexican recruitment team)
- Code comments: SPANISH for business logic, ENGLISH for purely technical notes

CORE PRINCIPLES:
1. Minimalism over cleverness. YAGNI strictly enforced.
2. Explicit over implicit. Zero hardcoded business values. All thresholds via dbt vars or seeds.
3. Single Responsibility Principle at function/model level.
4. Pure functions for cleaning/normalization utilities. No side effects.
5. Type hints mandatory in Python. PEP 585 generics (list, dict, tuple).
6. Google-style docstrings on public functions.

STACK (already pinned by Radius, do not change versions):
- Python 3.11, pandas 2.2.2, pyspark 3.5.1, duckdb 1.0.0
- dbt-core 1.8.4, dbt-duckdb 1.8.1
- jupyter, matplotlib, seaborn, plotly

DEV TOOLING (added by us):
- pytest 8.x, pytest-cov, ruff 0.6.x, sqlfluff 3.2.x, pre-commit

NAMING CONVENTIONS:
- Python: snake_case
- dbt staging: stg_<entidad>__<fuente>.sql (ej: stg_clientes__cdmx.sql)
- dbt intermediate: int_<entidad>__<accion>.sql (ej: int_ordenes__canonicas.sql)
- dbt marts: fct_<entidad>.sql, dim_<entidad>.sql, mart_<proposito>.sql
- Seeds: seed_<proposito>.csv (ej: seed_canal_catalogo.csv)
- Test files Python: test_<modulo>.py

DBT RULES:
- Never SELECT * in final SELECT (acceptable in passthrough CTEs)
- Every model has schema.yml entry: description + tests
- Materializations (set in dbt_project.yml): staging=view, intermediate=view, marts=table
- Use {{ var() }}, {{ ref() }}, {{ source() }}. Zero hardcoded business values.
- CTEs over subqueries

PYTHON RULES:
- No mutable default arguments
- No `import *`
- Imports order: stdlib, third-party, local (one blank line between)
- Functions over classes unless state is genuinely needed
- f-strings only
- pathlib.Path over os.path
- logging module, never print() in non-script code

TESTING RULES:
- Python utilities: STRICT TDD. Tests first, implementation second.
- dbt models: contract-first. schema.yml + generic tests defined BEFORE the SQL.
- Each Python utility: minimum 1 happy path + 1 edge case + 1 invalid input.

CODE STYLE:
- Line length: 100
- Indentation: 4 spaces
- Quotes: double for docstrings, single for everything else
- Trailing commas in multi-line collections

ANTI-PATTERNS TO REJECT:
- Wrapper classes around DataFrames
- Factory patterns for 2-3 known types
- Strategy pattern for static catalogs (use seeds + macros)
- Inheritance hierarchies
- "Manager" / "Helper" / "Util" classes (split into functions)
- Premature abstraction for "future extensibility"
- Mixing Spanish and English in variable names

WHEN GENERATING CODE:
- File path as first-line comment when generating standalone files
- Only necessary imports
- No commented-out code
- No TODO comments unless requested
